creator: jasonchu@nortelnetworks.com
text:
This situation is not that easy to reproduce for some machines, but when you 
try enough , it will happen like in a couple of days. But for certain machine, 
it happens all the time. 

I use Win2k and LAN to access Apache, it 's hard for me to reproduce.
But for some people as decribed as follows, it happens every time, and they 
uses Win98 and XP as client, DSL to access network.

One thing is for sure, it is reproduciable.

Here is the quote from them "

When using the Apache web proxy cache some sites do not fully display.  Such as 
pictures, format and placement, backgrounds.  Happens every time on 
www.msn.com  If you set IE to not use the web cache, directly access websites, 
works fine.  
"

For your information, here is part the Error.log for apache.
